# CSS Styling Rules

## CSS Variables
- Define color palette
- Define typography settings
- Define spacing units
- Define breakpoints

## Base Styles
- Reset default styles
- Set base typography
- Define container widths
- Set base colors

## Component Styles
- Header styling
- Hero section styling
- Featured dishes grid
- Menu section layout
- Why choose us section
- Footer styling

## Responsive Design Levels

### Level 1: Mobile First (Default)
- Base styles for mobile
- Single column layouts
- Appropriate font sizes
- Touch-friendly elements

### Level 2: Tablet (768px - 1023px)
- Two-column layouts
- Adjusted spacing
- Larger font sizes
- Enhanced navigation

### Level 3: Desktop (1024px and above)
- Multi-column layouts
- Maximum container width
- Optimized typography
- Hover effects

## Additional Features
- Dark mode support
- Reduced motion preferences
- Print styles
- High contrast mode

## Best Practices
- Use CSS Grid for 2D layouts
- Use Flexbox for 1D layouts
- Implement mobile-first approach
- Use CSS variables for consistency
- Keep specificity low
- Use BEM naming convention
- Optimize for performance
- Include fallbacks for older browsers

## Performance Guidelines
- Minimize CSS file size
- Use efficient selectors
- Optimize media queries
- Reduce repaints and reflows
- Use hardware acceleration when needed
- Implement lazy loading for images
- Minimize use of box-shadows and gradients
- Use transform and opacity for animations
